# Tech Stack

| Layer | Choice |
|---|---|
| Framework | Next.js 16.x — App Router, Turbopack |
| Language | TypeScript 5.x |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 with OKLCH theme variables |
| Components | shadcn/ui |
| Typography | Fraunces (display), Plus Jakarta Sans (body), JetBrains Mono (code) |
| Database | SQLite via Drizzle ORM + better-sqlite3 |
| Auth | NextAuth.js v5 (Credentials provider, JWT sessions) — Friend Release |
| Charts | Recharts |
| Drag & Drop | @dnd-kit/core |
| Date utils | date-fns |
| Theming | next-themes (light/dark toggle) |
| Testing | Vitest + React Testing Library |

# Testing Conventions

- Test files live in `src/lib/__tests__/` for pure logic, and alongside components as `*.test.tsx`.
- Run tests with `npm run test:run` (single pass) or `npm run test` (watch mode).
- Write tests for periodization logic, scheduler rules, and any pure functions. UI tests are optional.

# Commands

```bash
npm run dev        # Start dev server at localhost:3000
npm run build      # Production build
npm run test:run   # Run Vitest tests once
npx tsx src/scripts/<script>.ts  # Run one-off scripts (migrations, seeds)
```
